<td nowrap> <div style='position:absolute;left:11px;top:40px'>
<img src="g107014ex99_2s27gbgd.jpg" width="893" height="613" border="0" alt=""></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:12px;top:594px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>seabed&#45;to&#45;surface</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:12px;top:611px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>October 13, 2010</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:12px;top:627px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>slide 27</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:12px;top:3px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:35px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#CE142C;'>Adjusted EBITDA</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:10px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>(a)<font face='arial'> </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Adjusted EBITDA:&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:76px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>income taxation, depreciation and amortisation) as net income from continuing operations plus
finance costs, other gains </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:92px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and losses, taxation, depreciation and amortisation and
adjusted to exclude investment income and impairment of </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:108px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>property, plant and equipment
and intangibles. Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations is defined as Adjusted</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:124px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>EBITDA divided by revenue from continuing operations.&nbsp; Management believes that Adjusted
EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:140px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>margin from continuing operations are important indicators of
our operational strength and the performance of our </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:156px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>business. Adjusted EBITDA and
Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations have not been prepared in </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:172px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>accordance
with International Financial Reporting Standards (&#147;IFRS&#148;) as issued by the IASB nor as adopted for use in the </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:189px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>European Union.&nbsp; These non&#45;IFRS measures provide management with a meaningful
comparison amongst our various </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:205px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>regions, as they eliminate the effects of financing and
depreciation.&nbsp; Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:221px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>may also be a
useful ratio to compare our performance to our competitors and is widely used by shareholders and </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:237px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>analysts following the Group&#146;s performance. However, Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA
margin from continuing </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:253px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>operations as presented by the Group may not be comparable to
similarly titled measures reported by other companies.&nbsp; </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:269px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Such supplementary
adjustments to EBITDA may not be in accordance with current practices or the rules and regulations </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:286px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>adopted by the US Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;) that apply to
reports filed under the Securities </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:302px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Exchange Act of 1934.&nbsp; Accordingly, the SEC may
require that Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:318px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>continuing operations be
presented differently in filings made with the SEC than as presented in this release, or not be </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:334px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>presented at all. Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations are
not measures determined </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:350px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>in accordance with IFRS and should not be considered as an
alternative to, or more meaningful than, net income (as </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:366px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>determined in accordance with
IFRS), as a measure of the Group&#146;s operating results or cash flows from operations (as </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:383px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>determined in accordance with IFRS) or as a measure of the Group&#146;s liquidity.&nbsp; The
reconciliation of the Group&#146;s net </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:399px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>income from continuing operations to Adjusted
EBITDA from continuing operations is included in this release.&nbsp; This release</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:415px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>also
includes a supplemental calculation of Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations calculated as net operating </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:431px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>income from continuing operations, plus depreciation and amortisation and impairment charges
on property, plant and </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:447px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>equipment and intangibles.&nbsp; Management believes that this
supplemental presentation of Adjusted EBITDA from </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:463px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>continuing operations is also useful
as it is more in line with the presentation of similarly titled measures by companies </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:479px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>within Acergy&#146;s peer group and therefore believes it to be a helpful calculation for
those evaluating companies within </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:496px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Acergy&#146;s industry.&nbsp; Adjusted EBITDA for
discontinued operations is calculated as per methodology outlined above.&nbsp; </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:46px;top:512px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Adjusted
EBITDA for total operations is the total of continuing operations and discontinued operations. </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:190px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>The</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:220px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Group</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:264px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>calculates</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:336px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Adjusted</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:399px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>EBITDA</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:455px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>from</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:491px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>continuing</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:566px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>operations</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:641px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>(adjusted</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:710px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>earnings</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:772px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>before</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:820px;top:59px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>interest,</div> </td></tr></table></div>
